<p>As she entered CNRI that day, she noticed a figure sitting awkwardly in the corner of the waiting area. It was a young man, with short, brown hair, wearing thick glasses, and a slight paunch. She recognized him immediately as Nicolas, someone she had met years ago on a volunteering project. He had always been shy and withdrawn, but she had seen something in him that others had not.</p>
<p>Joanna approached him, and he looked up at her, his eyes hidden behind his glasses. "Joanna, it's great to see you," he said in a timid voice.</p>
<p>"Nicolas, it's great to see you too," Joanna replied, sitting down next to him. “I had no idea you worked here.” </p>
<p>"I joined CNRI a few months ago," Nicolas explained. "I was looking for a job where I could help people, and I thought this would be a good fit." </p>
<p>Joanna smiled warmly at him. "That's wonderful, Nicolas. I'm sure you're doing a terrific job."</p>
<p>They continued to chat for a few more minutes, catching up on old times before Laurel Lance appeared at the door. Joanna introduced Nicolas to Laurel and watched as they shook hands.</p>
<p>"So, what brings you to CNRI today, Joanna?" Laurel asked, narrowing her eyes slightly.</p>
<p>"I'm here to interview you for a piece I'm working on," Joanna explained, holding up her notepad. "I want to talk about your work here and how you're making a difference."</p>
<p>Laurel nodded, a small smile on her lips. She was grateful for the opportunity to talk about the work she cared so much about. "I'll do my best to give you some insights," she replied.</p>
<p>As they got to talking, Joanna glanced over at Nicolas, who was watching them with a look of reverence and admiration. She could tell that he was a fan of Laurel's too. They continued to chat for hours, sharing stories and ideas, and Joanna felt privileged to be in their company.</p>
<p>As the interview wrapped up, Laurel turned to Nicolas. "It was nice meeting you, Nicolas. Keep up the good work," she said, patting him on the shoulder.</p>
<p>"Thank you, Laurel. It means a lot coming from you," Nicolas replied, his voice shaking slightly.</p>
<p>As Joanna said her final goodbyes and headed out the door, she couldn't help but smile at the sight of Nicolas. She was happy to see that he had found a place where he belonged and was making a difference, just like Laurel had. She hoped that one day, he would find the strength within himself to break out of his shell and to let his light shine bright.</p></div>

