    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>As the evening continued and the attention shifted to the canine races, Ash couldn't help but feel uneasy about the earlier conversation involving potential breeding with other micro cheetahs. While he was grateful for Lance's continued protection and the improvements in their relationship, the idea of being used as a breeding tool for the whims of macros deeply disturbed him.</p>
<p>Lance, sensing the distress in his tiny companion, offered a gentle pat to Ash's head. "Don't worry, Ash. Your main priority is still to be my friend and companion. I won't pressure you into anything that you don't want to do, breeding included."</p>
<p>Ash looked up at Lance with cautious gratitude, relieved that at least, for now, he wouldn't be forced into a situation he disliked. As the night wore on, both the giant jaguar and the tiny pardinensis cheetah found solace in each other's company, their connection growing stronger and more understanding with each passing day.</p></div>

